  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Description: AT THE UPS FACILITY IN ANCHORAGE, ALASKA, A PACKAGE WAS UNABLE TO BE DELIVERED TO THE RECEIVER. PACKAGE INSPECTION OF CONTENTS FOUND FIVE X ONE POUND CONTAINERS OF ACCURATE 4350 SMOKELESS PROPELLANT CLASSIFIED AS NA3178, SMOKELESS POWDER FOR SMALL ARMS, 4.1 AND FIVE X ONE POUND CONTAINERS OF HODGDON H4350 RIFLE POWDER CLASSIFIED AS UN0161, POWDER, SMOKELESS, 1.3C. THERE ARE NO DANGEROUS GOODS MARKS OR LABELS ON THE OUTER BOX. IN ADDITION TO THE UPS STORE SHIPPING ADDRESS ON THE THERMAL LABEL, THERE IS ALSO A FROM LABEL OF BETTY ADKINS BROWN, 1287 GREENLAND ROAD, MEMPHIS TN 38134-7815. THERE IS AN INNER BOX THAT IS MARKED POWDER, SMOKLESS, UN0509 AND A 1.4C EXPLOSIVE DIAMOND LABEL.

  • Description: DURING PROCESSING AT THE EXPORT SORT IN ANCHORAGE, ALASKA, AN AIR PACKAGE SHIPPING FROM CANADA TO HONG KONG WAS DISCOVERED TO CONTAIN 19 CELL PHONES. THERMAL TRACKING LABEL SHOWS ANDROID TABLETS AS DESCRIPTION. INVOICE DESCRIPTION IS TABLETS. THERE ARE NO DANGEROUS GOODS MARKS OR LABELS ON THE OUTER BOX. NO LITHIUM BATTERY MARK ON THE OUTER BOX. THE CELL PHONES INSIDE THE BOX WERE INDIVIDUALLY WRAPPED AND ADDITIONALLY SURROUNDED BY BUBBLE WRAP. PRIOR TO DISCOVERY THE PACKAGE HAD FLOWN YVR TO SDF TO DISCOVERY IN ANC.

  • City: ANC
  • State: AK
  • Report Type: Undeclared Shipment with no Release
  • Mode Of Transportation: Air
  • Carrier/Reporter: ALASKA AIRLINES, INC.
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Description: May 4th, 2023. 7 of 8 pieces arrived on flight 175/04MAY. 1 piece was broken open and lithium-ion batteries fell out from the shipment. The RSA working on the inbound freight from the flight brought it to my attention and did further research. The batteries were not declared in this shipment, but nature of goods stated to be tools and clothes. This shipment originated in BOI and was screened TSA K9. I opened the box the rest of the way and did a physical search and discovered 3 - 20v lithium-ion batteries not attached to equipment. Did a physical search on the boxes that contained tools due to finding undeclared lithium-ion batteries. There were tools that the batteries could have attached to but were in two separate boxes.
